{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17539680","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17539680"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":0,"answeredAt":"2025-09-29T17:44:51+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-29T17:44:51+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"16693"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"16693","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/16693"},"attributes":{"optionProportions":[0.02,0.13,0.02,0.01,0.82]},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"9384"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"107186"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"9384","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/9384"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"16693"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"89639"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"22"},{"type":"tags","id":"66"},{"type":"tags","id":"72"},{"type":"tags","id":"76"},{"type":"tags","id":"1314"},{"type":"tags","id":"2166"},{"type":"tags","id":"2320"},{"type":"tags","id":"4149"},{"type":"tags","id":"12807"},{"type":"tags","id":"12915"},{"type":"tags","id":"12922"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"22202"},{"type":"contributions","id":"39759"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"107186","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/107186"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003EA 24-year-old woman presents to the early pregnancy clinic requesting termination of pregnancy. Her last menstrual period was six weeks ago, and a urine pregnancy test is positive. She has no significant medical history and takes no regular medications. She works full-time in retail and lives with her partner. She has made an informed decision after careful consideration and states she is not under any coercion. She asks for the quickest option and would prefer to avoid anaesthesia if possible.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EOn examination, she appears well with vital signs within normal limits. Ultrasound confirms an intrauterine pregnancy of 6 weeks gestation.\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following is the most appropriate management?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Surgical termination under general anaesthesia","Misoprostol alone","Expectant management with follow-up in one week","Referral for psychological counselling","Mifepristone followed by misoprostol"],"correctOptions":[4],"correctResponses":[],"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EThis patient presents requesting termination of pregnancy at six weeks gestation, confirmed by transvaginal ultrasound. Outpatient medical termination of pregnancy using the M2-2Step is safe and effective up to 63 days gestation, making this patient an appropriate candidate.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EMifepristone followed by misoprostol\u003C/strong\u003E is the gold standard regimen for medical termination of pregnancy - MS-2Step. Mifepristone blocks progesterone receptors leading to decidual breakdown. Misoprostol, given 24-48 hours later, causes uterine contractions and cervical softening. This regimen allows the patient to avoid surgery and general anaesthesia, with success rates over 95% at this gestation.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ESurgical termination\u003C/strong\u003E under general anaesthesia is unnecessarily invasive at this early gestation. While it remains a valid option, medical management is equally effective and this patient prefers an option that does not involve anaesthesia. \u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EMisoprostol alone\u003C/strong\u003E has lower efficacy (80-85%) compared to the combined regimen and is associated with more side effects including pain and prolonged bleeding. It should only be used when mifepristone is unavailable or contraindicated.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EExpectant management\u003C/strong\u003E would be inappropriate as the patient has made a clear and informed decision to terminate the pregnancy. Delaying management could result in the pregnancy progressing beyond the window for medical termination.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EReferral for psychological counselling\u003C/strong\u003E should be available but not mandatory when a patient has made an informed decision. This patient demonstrates clear decision-making capacity and shows no signs of distress or uncertainty requiring additional support.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":["","","","",""],"learningPoints":["Medical termination of pregnancy is safe and effective as an outpatient up to 63 days gestation using MS-2 Step","Mifepristone followed by misoprostol is the recommended regimen for medical termination of pregnancy","Ultrasound is essential to confirm intrauterine pregnancy and accurate gestational age","Mandatory psychological counselling is not required when a patient has made an informed decision"],"references":["True Relationships \u0026 Reproductive Health. Medical Termination of Pregnancy [Internet]. [cited 2024 Nov 29]. Available from: https://www.true.org.au/factsheets/choose-a-topic/medical-termination-of-pregnancy","Queensland Clinical Guidelines. Termination of pregnancy [Internet]. Brisbane: Queensland Health; 2024 Sep. Report No.: MN24.21-V10-R29. [cited 2024 Nov 29]. Available from: https://www.health.qld.gov.au/__data/assets/pdf_file/0029/735293/g-top.pdf"]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"89639"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"16693"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"89639","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/89639"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2025